        <item>
          <title>Gov. Newsom awards $131M to clear homeless encampments; Los Angeles gets $11.3M</title>
          <description><![CDATA[Gov. Gavin Newsom announced Friday that the state will grant 18 cities $131 million to clear homeless encampments and provide shelter, care and support. The grants are a part of the state’s $1 billion Encampment Resolution Funds. The city of Los Angeles is slated to receive $11.3 million in funding.]]></description>
